            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-25T03:51:27+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-25T03:51:27+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-24T17:21:27Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-24T17:21:27Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A broad trough lies over SA. A cold front clips the southeast as an upper trough moves up over SA today and tomorrow. A high pressure system develops south of the Bight late in the week and persists over the weekend.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
